 Raymond Carver, Mark Danielewski, Jennifer Egan, Tao Lin, David Mitchell, Joyce Carol Oates, Mary Robison, and Zadie Smith. Unpacking how the styles of these works detox, filter, binge, or ghost their worlds, Crisis Style is at once a taxonomy of contemporary cultural production and a theorization of action in a world always in need of repair. Ultimately, Dango presents a compelling argument for why we need aesthetic theory to understand what we're doing in our world today.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aAesthetics, Americany20th century. 0aAesthetics, Americany21st century. 0aArts, Americany20th century. 0aArts, Americany21st century. 0aArts, ModernxPhilosophy. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / American / General.2bisacsh  aAnscombe.  aaction.  aaffect.  acontrol.  acrisis.  aform.  aneoliberalism.  arecognition.  areparative.  awhiteness.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertStanford University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311073914540uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978150362956140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781503629561423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781503629561/original  a978-3-11-073914-5  Stanford University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021b2021  aGBV-deGruyter-alles